title: Randy Orton wins WWE Royal Rumble to earn spot at Wrestlemania 33 after eliminating Roman Reigns
text:
Sport Randy Orton wins WWE Royal Rumble to earn spot at Wrestlemania 33 after eliminating Roman Reigns Orton won the 30-man spectacular back in 2009 and repeated the trick as he eliminated Roman Reigns in San Antonio Share Click to play Tap to play The video will start in 8 Cancel Play now Randy Orton celebrates winning WWE Royal Rumble Share this video Get daily     
Randy Orton won a star-studded Royal Rumble to earn his spot at Wrestlemania 33. 
Orton won the 30-man spectacular back in 2009 and repeated the trick as he eliminated Roman Reigns. 
The Viper threw Reigns over the top rope following an RKO as he emerged victorious in San Antonio. 
Reigns had previously eliminated The Undertaker and looked to have overcome Bray Wyatt and Orton's double team attack. 
After throwing out Wyatt, he readied himself to spear Orton before being struck with an RKO. Randy Orton celebrates (Photo: WWE) Randy Orton celebrates (Photo: WWE) 
The Rumble flew by thanks to entertaining cameos from Manchester's umbrella-waving Jack Gallagher and NXT's 'Perfect 10' Tye Dillinger - out of course at number 10. 
Strowman eliminated seven men including powerhouse Mark Henry and the giant Big Show before Baron Corbin made a big statement by ending his rampage. 
Luke Harper turned on his master Wyatt, who was saved by Orton, dishing out trademark RKOs to everyone in sight. Roman Reigns makes his way to the ring (Photo: WWE) Action from the Wrestlemania (Photo: WWE) Royal Rumble (Photo: WWE) 
Brock Lesnar entering at number 26 was typically destructive but in the first of two shock moments was speared and hurled over the top rope by the WCW icon Goldberg. 
Undertaker than shocked the 52,000 strong crowd by awkwardly dumping out Goldberg, before Reigns emerged to colossal boos and blindsided The Phenom. 
The 2015 winner looked set for a second Rumble victory but Orton struck the crucial blow.
